Package: controller
Title: Controlled Vocabularies
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Joe",
           family = "Roe",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "joe@joeroe.io",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1011-1244"))
Description: Provides functions for working with controlled vocabularies.
  A controlled vocabulary is a predefined set of terms intended to be used to 
  be used in a specific context. This package introduces the 'control' verb, 
  which recodes values in a vector using a lookup table of preferred and 
  variant terms (a 'thesaurus'). It also includes functions for reading
  controlled vocabularies into R from standard formats.
